THE SON OF GOD<br/><br/>Jesus Christ, You came to save our lives;
<br />Jesus Christ, The Son of God!
<br /><br />Long ago in Bethlehem, t'was born a God-and-man,
<br />His name was Jesus Christ, He came and ask for hearts to repent.
<br /><br />But the little people said, &quot;You come to preach your dreams,
<br />but we just want a king.&quot; And they crucified their King!
<br /><br />Jesus Christ, You came to save our lives;
<br />Jesus Christ, You came to rid our crime;
<br />Jesus Christ, You bore our sin and shame;
<br />Jesus Christ, Lamb of God!
<br /><br />Now on this seventh day, let all our voices ring,
<br />we know that come what may, we have an Advocate to the King.
<br /><br />In eighteen forty-four, He trod the Holiest Place;
<br />Our scrolls read case-by-case, but His children have no fear!
<br /><br />Jesus Christ, The Way the Truth and Life;
<br />Jesus Christ, We sing Your song of triumph;
<br />Jesus Christ, Your blood on Calvary;
<br />Jesus Christ, Lamb of God!
<br /><br />Jesus Christ, You came to save our lives;
<br />Jesus Christ, You came to rid our crime;
<br />Jesus Christ, You bore our sin and shame;
<br />Jesus Christ, The Son of God!
<br /><br />Jesus Christ, The Son of God.....!
<br /><br />JESUS CHRIST!
